parameters: \N<Bright Madame>Oh, are you perhaps one of the guards?

\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I'm not a guard, but I work as a knight in the

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>That's right. It's the knight's duty to protect

\CE[79]\CE[78]\CE[83]\CE[84]\OC[31]\N<Rain>As \....\....\. mentioned, I witnessed someone

\N<Bright Madame>Well, if something like this happens again, let's

\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I apologize for not being flexible and causing you

\CE[79]\N<Bright Madame>I suppose there's no helping it. Knights and
guards don't have the freedom to punish as they

\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Thank you for your understanding. Well then... if
